Config + driver ported to gomc (LIB:linuxcnc.hal + PARAMETER_FILE; test.sh drives
a resident gomc-server; test-ui.py on the gmi client).

Fails on JOG OVERSHOOT: the driver does a continuous jog toward an increment
target and calls jog_stop when it reads the target position from gmi.Stat, but
gmi's WebSocket status lags, so the axis is seen at the target late and overshoots
(e.g. jog to -0.500 ends at -1.012 -> "jogged axis 0 past target"). Needs either
a gomc-side fix (tighter jog-stop, or honor jog increment/limit so continuous jog
stops itself at the target) or a driver change (use gmi incremental jog, or read
the live position pin via halcmd instead of the lagged Stat). Investigate whether
gomc supports bounded/incremental jog that stops itself; remove this xfail once
jog stops at the commanded target.

(NB: a prior conversion reported this as passing; it does not pass on a clean
re-run — the overshoot is timing-sensitive.)
